    <section id="cid6"><title>Acceleration</title><definition id="fhsst_id1326"><term id="termfhsst_id1326"> Acceleration </term> <meaning id="meaningfhsst_id1326">
      <para id="id67550">Acceleration is the rate of change of velocity. </para>
      </meaning></definition>
      <para id="id67562">Acceleration (symbol <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>a</m:mi></m:math>) is the rate of change of velocity. It is a measure of how fast the velocity of an object changes in time. If we have a change in velocity (<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>Δ</m:mi><m:mi>v</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>) over a time interval (<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>Δ</m:mi><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>), then the acceleration (<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>a</m:mi></m:math>) is defined as:</para>
      <equation id="id67610">
        <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mi> acceleration </m:mi>
              <m:mspace width="4pt"/>
              <m:mo>(</m:mo>
              <m:mi> in </m:mi>
              <m:mspace width="4pt"/>
              <m:mi mathvariant="normal">m</m:mi>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mo>·</m:mo>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mi mathvariant="normal">s</m:mi>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo>)</m:mo>
              <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mfrac>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi> change </m:mi>
                  <m:mspace width="4pt"/>
                  <m:mi> in </m:mi>
                  <m:mspace width="4pt"/>
                  <m:mi> velocity </m:mi>
                  <m:mspace width="4pt"/>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                  <m:mi> in </m:mi>
                  <m:mspace width="4pt"/>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="normal">m</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:msup>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="normal">s</m:mi>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:msup>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mi> change </m:mi>
                <m:mspace width="4pt"/>
